🚀 Student Performance Analyzer System
📌 Project Overview

Welcome to my first GitHub project! 🎉
The Student Performance Analyzer System is a Python-based application designed to analyze students’ academic performance in an efficient and structured way.

This system calculates totals, averages, percentages, grades, and rankings to provide a complete academic overview of each student.

It also helps in:

Identifying top performers 🏆
Highlighting students who need improvement 📉
Generating a clear performance summary report 📊
🎯 Key Features
📊 Calculate total marks, average, and percentage
🏅 Assign grades based on performance
🥇 Identify top-performing students
⚠️ Detect students needing improvement
📄 Generate structured performance reports
🧠 Simple logic using Python fundamentals
🛠️ Technologies Used
Python 🐍
Basic Data Structures (Lists, Loops, Conditions)
Console-Based Application
📈 Project Purpose

This project demonstrates:

Fundamental data analysis skills
Problem-solving using Python
Logic building for real-world academic systems
Beginner-level software development practice
🚀 How to Run

Clone the repository:

git clone https://github.com/your-username/Student-Performance-Analyzer-System-Project.git

Navigate to the project folder:

cd Student-Performance-Analyzer-System-Project

Run the Python file:

python main.py
